ieces (approx. 1 in.)","3 oz Parmesan cheese, cut into pieces (approx. ½ in.)","3 oz provolone cheese, cut into pieces (approx. 1 in.)","3 oz cheddar cheese, cut into pieces (approx. 1 in.)","12 ½ oz ripe tomatoes, cut into pieces (approx. 1 in.)","1 oz olive oil","½ tsp salt","1 tsp dried oregano"]},{"title":"Vegetable Toppings","content":["2 garlic cloves","1 oz olive oil","2 oz zucchini, cut into cubes","3 oz leeks, sliced","2 ½ oz canned sweet corn kernels, drained"]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["8 all beef hot dogs, cut into slices","dried oregano, to taste","5 ½ oz ham, cut into cubes (¼ in. x ¼ in.)","fresh baby spinach, to taste"]}],"id":"r111405","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-66sb-m4V3so\/XZan17xwj4I\/AAAAAAAAhEg\/HqRnVDHQAPMutqVA1M9WLsHd8OOgtfB3wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_WCxUlQU4YtJpxBAX.png","title":"Mini Pizzas","publishedAt":"2017-03-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7 g","fat":"10 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"24 g","calories":"920 kJ \/ 220 kcal"},"usefulItems":"parchment paper, kitchen towel, rolling pin, baking sheets (approx. 16 in. x 14 in.), oven","hintsAndTricks":["Let the kids personalize their own pizzas.","Be creative and try different toppings such as: pre-cooked sausage, ham and pineapple, spinach, mushrooms or basil."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","1h 30m","18 pieces"]}